This function crops or pads each video to match a target resolution without scaling
and a offset in every direction is also possible.

# Description
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- If the input video is **larger**, a centered region is cropped (with optional offset).
- If the input is **smaller**, it is centered and padded with black borders.
- Resolution is preserved; videos are never scaled.

# Arguments (Flags)
#---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- `--files`              	Input files or patterns (e.g. `video01.mp4`, `sample%.mkv`)
- `--resolution WxH`     	Target resolution (e.g. `1920x1080`)
- `--offset-x VALUE`     	Horizontal offset from center when cropping/padding (default: 0)
- `--offset-y VALUE`     	Vertical offset from center when cropping/padding (default: 0)
- `--output FILE`        	Optional: custom output filename [.mp4 added if missing]

# Behavior
#------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Files like `clip%.mp4` are expanded using `%` as wildcard placeholder
- Each input is processed and saved individually
- Output filenames default to `<name>_WxH.mp4` unless overridden

# Examples
#---------------------------------------------------------------------------
video crop-pad --files test01.mp4 --resolution 1920x1080
video crop-pad sample%.mp4 --resolution 1280x720 --offset-x 50
video crop-pad --files input01.mp4 --resolution 1024x768 --output result.mp4


#---
Note: If the crop region would fall outside the video bounds due to offset, the file is skipped.

